23void Disassemble(const WasmModule* module, ModuleWireBytes wire_bytes,
24 NamesProvider* names,
25 v8::debug::DisassemblyCollector* collector,
26 std::vector<int>* function_body_offsets) {
27 MultiLineStringBuilder out;
28 AccountingAllocator allocator;
29 ModuleDisassembler md(out, module, names, wire_bytes, &allocator,
30 /* no offsets yet */ {}, function_body_offsets);
31 md.PrintModule({0, 2}, v8_flags.wasm_disassembly_max_mb);
32 out.ToDisassemblyCollector(collector);
33}
34
35void Disassemble(base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes,
36 v8::debug::DisassemblyCollector* collector,
37 std::vector<int>* function_body_offsets) {
38 std::unique_ptr<OffsetsProvider> offsets = AllocateOffsetsProvider();
39 ModuleResult result =
40 DecodeWasmModuleForDisassembler(wire_bytes, offsets.get());
41 MultiLineStringBuilder out;
42 AccountingAllocator allocator;
43 if (result.failed()) {
44 WasmError error = result.error();
45 out << "Decoding error: " << error.message() << " at offset "
46 << error.offset();
47 out.ToDisassemblyCollector(collector);
48 return;
49 }
50 const WasmModule* module = result.value().get();
51 NamesProvider names(module, wire_bytes);
52 ModuleWireBytes module_bytes(wire_bytes);
53 ModuleDisassembler md(out, module, &names, module_bytes, &allocator,
54 std::move(offsets), function_body_offsets);
55 md.PrintModule({0, 2}, v8_flags.wasm_disassembly_max_mb);
56 out.ToDisassemblyCollector(collector);
57}
58
59void MultiLineStringBuilder::ToDisassemblyCollector(
60 v8::debug::DisassemblyCollector* collector) {
61 if (length() != 0) NextLine(0); // Finalize last line.
62 collector->ReserveLineCount(lines_.size());
63 for (const Line& l : lines_) {
64 // Don't include trailing '\n'.
65 collector->AddLine(l.data, l.len - 1, l.bytecode_offset);
66 }
67}
68
69void DisassembleFunctionImpl(const WasmModule* module, int func_index,
70 base::Vector<const uint8_t> function_body,
71 ModuleWireBytes module_bytes, NamesProvider* names,
72 std::ostream& os, std::vector<uint32_t>* offsets) {
73 MultiLineStringBuilder sb;
74 const wasm::WasmFunction& func = module->functions[func_index];
75 AccountingAllocator allocator;
76 Zone zone(&allocator, "Wasm disassembler");
77 bool shared = module->types[func.sig_index].is_shared;
78 WasmFeatures detected;
79 FunctionBodyDisassembler d(&zone, module, func_index, shared, &detected,
80 func.sig, function_body.begin(),
81 function_body.end(), func.code.offset(),
82 module_bytes, names);
83 d.DecodeAsWat(sb, {0, 2}, FunctionBodyDisassembler::kPrintHeader);
84 const bool print_offsets = false;
85 sb.WriteTo(os, print_offsets, offsets);
86}
87
88void DisassembleFunction(const WasmModule* module, int func_index,
89 base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes,
90 NamesProvider* names, std::ostream& os) {
91 DCHECK(func_index < static_cast<int>(module->functions.size()) &&
92 func_index >= static_cast<int>(module->num_imported_functions));
93 ModuleWireBytes module_bytes(wire_bytes);
94 base::Vector<const uint8_t> code =
95 module_bytes.GetFunctionBytes(&module->functions[func_index]);
96 std::vector<uint32_t>* collect_offsets = nullptr;
97 DisassembleFunctionImpl(module, func_index, code, module_bytes, names, os,
98 collect_offsets);
99}
100
101void DisassembleFunction(const WasmModule* module, int func_index,
102 base::Vector<const uint8_t> function_body,
103 base::Vector<const uint8_t> maybe_wire_bytes,
104 uint32_t function_body_offset, std::ostream& os,
105 std::vector<uint32_t>* offsets) {
106 DCHECK(func_index < static_cast<int>(module->functions.size()) &&
107 func_index >= static_cast<int>(module->num_imported_functions));
108 NamesProvider fake_names(module, maybe_wire_bytes);
109 DisassembleFunctionImpl(module, func_index, function_body,
110 ModuleWireBytes{nullptr, 0}, &fake_names, os,
111 offsets);
112}

117static constexpr char kHexChars[] = "0123456789abcdef";
118static constexpr char kUpperHexChars[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
119
120// Returns the log2 of the alignment, e.g. "4" means 2<<4 == 16 bytes.
121// This is the same format as used in .wasm binary modules.
122uint32_t GetDefaultAlignment(WasmOpcode opcode) {
123 switch (opcode) {
124 case kExprS128LoadMem:
125 case kExprS128StoreMem:
126 return 4;
127 case kExprS128Load8x8S:
128 case kExprS128Load8x8U:
129 case kExprS128Load16x4S:
130 case kExprS128Load16x4U:
131 case kExprS128Load32x2S:
132 case kExprS128Load32x2U:
133 case kExprS128Load64Splat:
134 case kExprS128Load64Zero:
135 case kExprS128Load64Lane:
136 case kExprS128Store64Lane:
137 return 3;
138 case kExprS128Load32Splat:
139 case kExprS128Load32Zero:
140 case kExprS128Load32Lane:
141 case kExprS128Store32Lane:
142 return 2;
143 case kExprS128Load16Splat:
144 case kExprS128Load16Lane:
145 case kExprS128Store16Lane:
146 return 1;
147 case kExprS128Load8Splat:
148 case kExprS128Load8Lane:
149 case kExprS128Store8Lane:
150 return 0;
151
152#define CASE(Opcode, ...) \
153 case kExpr##Opcode: \
154 return GetLoadType(kExpr##Opcode).size_log_2();
155 FOREACH_LOAD_MEM_OPCODE(CASE)
156#undef CASE
157#define CASE(Opcode, ...) \
158 case kExpr##Opcode: \
159 return GetStoreType(kExpr##Opcode).size_log_2();
160 FOREACH_STORE_MEM_OPCODE(CASE)
161#undef CASE
162
163#define CASE(Opcode, Type) \
164 case kExpr##Opcode: \
165 return ElementSizeLog2Of(MachineType::Type().representation());
166 ATOMIC_OP_LIST(CASE)
167 ATOMIC_STORE_OP_LIST(CASE)
168#undef CASE
169
170 default:
171 UNREACHABLE();
172 }
173}
174
175void PrintSignatureOneLine(StringBuilder& out, const FunctionSig* sig,
176 uint32_t func_index, NamesProvider* names,
177 bool param_names,
178 IndexAsComment indices_as_comments) {
179 if (param_names) {
180 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); i++) {
181 out << " (param ";
182 names->PrintLocalName(out, func_index, i, indices_as_comments);
183 out << ' ';
184 names->PrintValueType(out, sig->GetParam(i));
185 out << ")";
186 }
187 } else if (sig->parameter_count() > 0) {
188 out << " (param";
189 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); i++) {
190 out << " ";
191 names->PrintValueType(out, sig->GetParam(i));
192 }
193 out << ")";
194 }
195 for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->return_count(); i++) {
196 out << " (result ";
197 names->PrintValueType(out, sig->GetReturn(i));
198 out << ")";
199 }
200}
201
202void PrintStringRaw(StringBuilder& out, const uint8_t* start,
203 const uint8_t* end) {
204 for (const uint8_t* ptr = start; ptr < end; ptr++) {
205 uint8_t b = *ptr;
206 if (b < 32 || b >= 127 || b == '"' || b == '\\') {
207 out << '\\' << kHexChars[b >> 4] << kHexChars[b & 0xF];
208 } else {
209 out << static_cast<char>(b);
210 }
211 }
212}

215// FunctionBodyDisassembler.
216
217void FunctionBodyDisassembler::DecodeAsWat(MultiLineStringBuilder& out,
218 Indentation indentation,
219 FunctionHeader include_header,
220 uint32_t* first_instruction_offset) {
221 out_ = &out;
222 int base_indentation = indentation.current();
223 // Print header.
224 if (include_header == kPrintHeader) {
225 out << indentation << "(func ";
226 names_->PrintFunctionName(out, func_index_, NamesProvider::kDevTools);
227 PrintSignatureOneLine(out, sig_, func_index_, names_, true,
228 kIndicesAsComments);
229 out.NextLine(pc_offset());
230 } else {
231 out.set_current_line_bytecode_offset(pc_offset());
232 }
233 indentation.increase();
234
235 // Decode and print locals.
236 uint32_t locals_length = DecodeLocals(pc_);
237 if (failed()) {
238 // TODO(jkummerow): Improve error handling.
239 out << "Failed to decode locals\n";
240 return;
241 }
242 for (uint32_t i = static_cast<uint32_t>(sig_->parameter_count());
243 i < num_locals_; i++) {
244 out << indentation << "(local ";
245 names_->PrintLocalName(out, func_index_, i);
246 out << " ";
247 names_->PrintValueType(out, local_type(i));
248 out << ")";
249 out.NextLine(pc_offset());
250 }
251 consume_bytes(locals_length);
252 out.set_current_line_bytecode_offset(pc_offset());
253 if (first_instruction_offset) *first_instruction_offset = pc_offset();
254
255 // Main loop.
256 while (pc_ < end_ && ok()) {
257 WasmOpcode opcode = GetOpcode();
258 current_opcode_ = opcode; // Some immediates need to know this.
259
260 // Deal with indentation.
261 if (opcode == kExprEnd || opcode == kExprElse || opcode == kExprCatch ||
262 opcode == kExprCatchAll || opcode == kExprDelegate) {
263 if (indentation.current() >= base_indentation) {
264 indentation.decrease();
265 }
266 }
267 out << indentation;
268 if (opcode == kExprElse || opcode == kExprCatch ||
269 opcode == kExprCatchAll || opcode == kExprBlock || opcode == kExprIf ||
270 opcode == kExprLoop || opcode == kExprTry || opcode == kExprTryTable) {
271 indentation.increase();
272 }
273
274 // Print the opcode and its immediates.
275 if (opcode == kExprEnd) {
276 if (indentation.current() < base_indentation) {
277 out << ";; Unexpected end byte";
278 } else if (indentation.current() == base_indentation) {
279 out << ")"; // End of the function.
280 } else {
281 out << "end";
282 const LabelInfo& label = label_stack_.back();
283 if (label.start != nullptr) {
284 out << " ";
285 out.write(label.start, label.length);
286 }
287 label_stack_.pop_back();
288 }
289 } else {
290 out << WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode);
291 }
292 if (opcode == kExprBlock || opcode == kExprIf || opcode == kExprLoop ||
293 opcode == kExprTry || opcode == kExprTryTable) {
294 // Create the LabelInfo now to get the correct offset, but only push it
295 // after printing the immediates because the immediates don't see the new
296 // label yet.
297 LabelInfo label(out.line_number(), out.length(),
298 label_occurrence_index_++);
299 pc_ += PrintImmediatesAndGetLength(out);
300 label_stack_.push_back(label);
301 } else {
302 pc_ += PrintImmediatesAndGetLength(out);
303 }
304
305 out.NextLine(pc_offset());
306 }
307
308 if (pc_ != end_) {
309 // TODO(jkummerow): Improve error handling.
310 out << "Beyond end of code";
311 }
312}
313
314void FunctionBodyDisassembler::DecodeGlobalInitializer(StringBuilder& out) {
315 while (pc_ < end_) {
316 WasmOpcode opcode = GetOpcode();
317 current_opcode_ = opcode; // Some immediates need to know this.
318 // Don't print the final "end".
319 if (opcode == kExprEnd && pc_ + 1 == end_) break;
320 uint32_t length;
321 out << " (" << WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(opcode);
322 length = PrintImmediatesAndGetLength(out);
323 out << ")";
324 pc_ += length;
325 }
326}
327
328WasmOpcode FunctionBodyDisassembler::GetOpcode() {
329 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(*pc_);
330 if (!WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) return opcode;
331 return read_prefixed_opcode<ValidationTag>(pc_).first;
332}
333
334void FunctionBodyDisassembler::PrintHexNumber(StringBuilder& out,
335 uint64_t number) {
336 constexpr size_t kBufferSize = sizeof(number) * 2 + 2; // +2 for "0x".
337 char buffer[kBufferSize];
338 char* end = buffer + kBufferSize;
339 char* ptr = end;
340 do {
341 *(--ptr) = kHexChars[number & 0xF];
342 number >>= 4;
343 } while (number > 0);
344 *(--ptr) = 'x';
345 *(--ptr) = '0';
346 size_t length = static_cast<size_t>(end - ptr);
347 char* output = out.allocate(length);
348 memcpy(output, ptr, length);
349}

354template <typename ValidationTag>
355class ImmediatesPrinter {
356 public:
357 ImmediatesPrinter(StringBuilder& out, FunctionBodyDisassembler* owner)
358 : out_(out), owner_(owner) {}
359
360 void PrintDepthAsLabel(int imm_depth) {
361 out_ << " ";
362 size_t label_start_position = out_.length();
363 int depth = imm_depth;
364 if (owner_->current_opcode_ == kExprDelegate) depth++;
365 // Be robust: if the module is invalid, print what we got.
366 if (depth < 0 || depth >= static_cast<int>(owner_->label_stack_.size())) {
367 out_ << imm_depth;
368 return;
369 }
370 // If the label's name has already been determined and backpatched, just
371 // copy it here.
372 LabelInfo& label_info = owner_->label_info(depth);
373 if (label_info.start != nullptr) {
374 out_.write(label_info.start, label_info.length);
375 return;
376 }
377 // Determine the label's name and backpatch the line that opened the block.
378 names()->PrintLabelName(out_, owner_->func_index_,
379 label_info.name_section_index,
380 owner_->label_generation_index_++);
381 label_info.length = out_.length() - label_start_position;
382 owner_->out_->PatchLabel(label_info, out_.start() + label_start_position);
383 }
384
385 void PrintSignature(uint32_t sig_index) {
386 if (owner_->module_->has_signature(sig_index)) {
387 const FunctionSig* sig = owner_->module_->signature(sig_index);
388 PrintSignatureOneLine(out_, sig, 0 /* ignored */, names(), false);
389 } else {
390 out_ << " (signature: " << sig_index << " INVALID)";
391 }
392 }

395 if (imm.sig.all().begin() == nullptr) {

397 } else {
398 PrintSignatureOneLine(out_, &imm.sig, 0 /* ignored */, names(), false);
399 }
400 }

413 if (imm.type.is_index()) use_type(imm.type.ref_index());

416 void BranchDepth(BranchDepthImmediate& imm) { PrintDepthAsLabel(imm.depth); }

418 void BranchTable(BranchTableImmediate& imm) {
419 const uint8_t* pc = imm.table;
420 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= imm.table_count; i++) {
421 auto [target, length] = owner_->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc);
422 PrintDepthAsLabel(target);
423 pc += length;
424 }

427 const char* CatchKindToString(CatchKind kind) {
428 switch (kind) {
429 case kCatch:
430 return "catch";
431 case kCatchRef:
432 return "catch_ref";
433 case kCatchAll:
434 return "catch_all";
435 case kCatchAllRef:
436 return "catch_all_ref";
437 default:
438 return "<invalid>";
439 }
440 }
441
442 void TryTable(TryTableImmediate& imm) {
443 const uint8_t* pc = imm.table;
444 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < imm.table_count; i++) {
445 uint8_t kind = owner_->read_u8<ValidationTag>(pc);
446 pc += 1;
447 out_ << " " << CatchKindToString(static_cast<CatchKind>(kind));
448 if (kind == kCatch || kind == kCatchRef) {
449 auto [tag, length] = owner_->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc);
450 out_ << " ";
451 names()->PrintTagName(out_, tag);
452 pc += length;
453 }
454 auto [target, length] = owner_->read_u32v<ValidationTag>(pc);
455 PrintDepthAsLabel(target);
456 pc += length;
457 }
458 }

550
551 void F32Const(ImmF32Immediate& imm) {
552 float f = imm.value;
553 if (f == 0) {
554 out_ << (1 / f < 0 ? " -0.0" : " 0.0");
555 } else if (std::isinf(f)) {
556 out_ << (f > 0 ? " inf" : " -inf");
557 } else if (std::isnan(f)) {
558 uint32_t bits = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(f);
559 uint32_t payload = bits & 0x7F'FFFFu;
560 uint32_t signbit = bits >> 31;
561 if (payload == 0x40'0000u) {
562 out_ << (signbit == 1 ? " -nan" : " nan");
563 } else {
564 out_ << (signbit == 1 ? " -nan:" : " +nan:");
565 owner_->PrintHexNumber(out_, payload);
566 }
567 } else {
568 std::ostringstream o;
569 // TODO(dlehmann): Change to `std::format` (C++20) or to `std::to_chars`
570 // (C++17) once available, so that `0.1` isn't printed as `0.100000001`
571 // any more.
572 o << std::setprecision(std::numeric_limits<float>::max_digits10) << f;
573 out_ << " " << o.str();
574 }
575 }
576
577 void F64Const(ImmF64Immediate& imm) {
578 double d = imm.value;
579 if (d == 0) {
580 out_ << (1 / d < 0 ? " -0.0" : " 0.0");
581 } else if (std::isinf(d)) {
582 out_ << (d > 0 ? " inf" : " -inf");
583 } else if (std::isnan(d)) {
584 uint64_t bits = base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(d);
585 uint64_t payload = bits & 0xF'FFFF'FFFF'FFFFull;
586 uint64_t signbit = bits >> 63;
587 if (payload == 0x8'0000'0000'0000ull) {
588 out_ << (signbit == 1 ? " -nan" : " nan");
589 } else {
590 out_ << (signbit == 1 ? " -nan:" : " +nan:");
591 owner_->PrintHexNumber(out_, payload);
592 }
593 } else {
594 char buffer[100];
595 const char* str = DoubleToCString(d, base::VectorOf(buffer, 100u));
596 out_ << " " << str;
597 }
598 }
599
600 void S128Const(Simd128Immediate& imm) {
601 if (owner_->current_opcode_ == kExprI8x16Shuffle) {
602 for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
603 out_ << " " << uint32_t{imm.value[i]};
604 }
605 } else {
606 DCHECK_EQ(owner_->current_opcode_, kExprS128Const);
607 out_ << " i32x4";
608 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
609 out_ << " 0x";
610 for (int j = 3; j >= 0; j--) { // Little endian.
611 uint8_t b = imm.value[i * 4 + j];
612 out_ << kUpperHexChars[b >> 4];
613 out_ << kUpperHexChars[b & 0xF];
614 }
615 }
616 }
617 }
618
619 void StringConst(StringConstImmediate& imm) {
620 if (imm.index >= owner_->module_->stringref_literals.size()) {
621 out_ << " " << imm.index << " INVALID";
622 return;
623 }
624 if (owner_->wire_bytes_.start() == nullptr) {
625 out_ << " " << imm.index;
626 return;
627 }
628 out_ << " \"";
629 const WasmStringRefLiteral& lit =
630 owner_->module_->stringref_literals[imm.index];
631 const uint8_t* start = owner_->wire_bytes_.start() + lit.source.offset();
632 static constexpr uint32_t kMaxCharsPrinted = 40;
633 if (lit.source.length() <= kMaxCharsPrinted) {
634 const uint8_t* end =
635 owner_->wire_bytes_.start() + lit.source.end_offset();
636 PrintStringRaw(out_, start, end);
637 } else {
638 const uint8_t* end = start + kMaxCharsPrinted - 1;
639 PrintStringRaw(out_, start, end);
640 out_ << "";
641 }
642 out_ << '"';
643 if (kIndicesAsComments) out_ << " (;" << imm.index << ";)";
644 }

654 out_ << " " << uint32_t{imm.memory_src.index};
655 }

669
670 void ArrayCopy(IndexImmediate& dst, IndexImmediate& src) {
671 out_ << " ";
672 names()->PrintTypeName(out_, dst.index);
673 out_ << " ";
674 names()->PrintTypeName(out_, src.index);
675 use_type(dst.index);
676 use_type(src.index);
677 }
678
679 private:
680 void use_type(uint32_t type_index) { owner_->used_types_.insert(type_index); }
681
682 NamesProvider* names() { return owner_->names_; }
683
684 uint32_t func_index() { return owner_->func_index_; }
685
686 StringBuilder& out_;
687 FunctionBodyDisassembler* owner_;
688};
689
690uint32_t FunctionBodyDisassembler::PrintImmediatesAndGetLength(
691 StringBuilder& out) {
692 using Printer = ImmediatesPrinter<ValidationTag>;
693 Printer imm_printer(out, this);
694 return WasmDecoder::OpcodeLength<Printer>(this, this->pc_, imm_printer);
695}

698// OffsetsProvider.
699
700void OffsetsProvider::CollectOffsets(const WasmModule* module,
701 base::Vector<const uint8_t> wire_bytes) {
702 num_imported_tables_ = module->num_imported_tables;
703 num_imported_globals_ = module->num_imported_globals;
704 num_imported_tags_ = module->num_imported_tags;
705 type_offsets_.reserve(module->types.size());
706 import_offsets_.reserve(module->import_table.size());
707 table_offsets_.reserve(module->tables.size() - num_imported_tables_);
708 tag_offsets_.reserve(module->tags.size() - num_imported_tags_);
709 global_offsets_.reserve(module->globals.size() - num_imported_globals_);
710 element_offsets_.reserve(module->elem_segments.size());
711 data_offsets_.reserve(module->data_segments.size());
712 recgroups_.reserve(4); // We can't know, so this is just a guess.
713
714 ModuleDecoderImpl decoder{WasmFeatures::All(), wire_bytes, kWasmOrigin, this};
715 constexpr bool kNoVerifyFunctions = false;
716 decoder.DecodeModule(kNoVerifyFunctions);
717}

720// ModuleDisassembler.
721
722ModuleDisassembler::ModuleDisassembler(
723 MultiLineStringBuilder& out, const WasmModule* module, NamesProvider* names,
724 const ModuleWireBytes wire_bytes, AccountingAllocator* allocator,
725 std::unique_ptr<OffsetsProvider> offsets_provider,
726 std::vector<int>* function_body_offsets)
727 : out_(out),
728 module_(module),
729 names_(names),
730 wire_bytes_(wire_bytes),
731 start_(wire_bytes_.start()),
732 zone_(allocator, "disassembler zone"),
733 offsets_(offsets_provider.release()),
734 function_body_offsets_(function_body_offsets) {
735 if (!offsets_) {
736 offsets_ = std::make_unique<OffsetsProvider>();
737 offsets_->CollectOffsets(module, wire_bytes_.module_bytes());
738 }
739}

742
743void ModuleDisassembler::PrintTypeDefinition(uint32_t type_index,
744 Indentation indentation,
745 IndexAsComment index_as_comment) {
746 uint32_t offset = offsets_->type_offset(type_index);
747 out_.NextLine(offset);
748 out_ << indentation << "(type ";
749 names_->PrintTypeName(out_, type_index, index_as_comment);
750 const TypeDefinition& type = module_->types[type_index];
751 bool has_super = type.supertype != kNoSuperType;
752 if (has_super) {
753 out_ << " (sub ";
754 if (type.is_final) out_ << "final ";
755 names_->PrintHeapType(out_, HeapType(type.supertype));
756 }
757 if (type.kind == TypeDefinition::kArray) {
758 const ArrayType* atype = type.array_type;
759 out_ << " (array";
760 if (type.is_shared) out_ << " shared";
761 out_ << " (field ";
762 PrintMutableType(atype->mutability(), atype->element_type());
763 out_ << ")"; // Closes "(field ...".
764 } else if (type.kind == TypeDefinition::kStruct) {
765 const StructType* stype = type.struct_type;
766 out_ << " (struct";
767 if (type.is_shared) out_ << " shared";
768 bool break_lines = stype->field_count() > 2;
769 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < stype->field_count(); i++) {
770 LineBreakOrSpace(break_lines, indentation, offset);
771 out_ << "(field ";
772 names_->PrintFieldName(out_, type_index, i);
773 out_ << " ";
774 PrintMutableType(stype->mutability(i), stype->field(i));
775 out_ << ")";
776 }
777 } else if (type.kind == TypeDefinition::kFunction) {
778 const FunctionSig* sig = type.function_sig;
779 out_ << " (func";
780 if (type.is_shared) out_ << " shared";
781 bool break_lines = sig->parameter_count() + sig->return_count() > 2;
782 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); i++) {
783 LineBreakOrSpace(break_lines, indentation, offset);
784 out_ << "(param ";
785 names_->PrintLocalName(out_, type_index, i);
786 out_ << " ";
787 names_->PrintValueType(out_, sig->GetParam(i));
788 out_ << ")";
789 }
790 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < sig->return_count(); i++) {
791 LineBreakOrSpace(break_lines, indentation, offset);
792 out_ << "(result ";
793 names_->PrintValueType(out_, sig->GetReturn(i));
794 out_ << ")";
795 }
796 }
797 // Closes "(type", "(sub", and "(array" / "(struct" / "(func".
798 out_ << (has_super ? ")))" : "))");
799}
800
801void ModuleDisassembler::PrintModule(Indentation indentation, size_t max_mb) {
802 // 0. General infrastructure.
803 // We don't store import/export information on {WasmTag} currently.
804 size_t num_tags = module_->tags.size();
805 std::vector<bool> exported_tags(num_tags, false);
806 for (const WasmExport& ex : module_->export_table) {
807 if (ex.kind == kExternalTag) exported_tags[ex.index] = true;
808 }
809
810 // I. Module name.
811 out_ << indentation << "(module";
812 if (module_->name.is_set()) {
813 out_ << " $";
814 const uint8_t* name_start = start_ + module_->name.offset();
815 out_.write(name_start, module_->name.length());
816 }
817 indentation.increase();
818
819 // II. Types
820 uint32_t recgroup_index = 0;
821 OffsetsProvider::RecGroup recgroup = offsets_->recgroup(recgroup_index++);
822 bool in_explicit_recgroup = false;
823 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < module_->types.size(); i++) {
824 // No need to check {recgroup.valid()}, as the comparison will simply
825 // never be true otherwise.
826 while (i == recgroup.start_type_index) {
827 out_.NextLine(recgroup.offset);
828 out_ << indentation << "(rec";
829 if V8_UNLIKELY (recgroup.end_type_index == i) {
830 // Empty recgroup.
831 out_ << ")";
832 DCHECK(!in_explicit_recgroup);
833 recgroup = offsets_->recgroup(recgroup_index++);
834 continue;
835 } else {
836 in_explicit_recgroup = true;
837 indentation.increase();
838 break;
839 }
840 }
841 if (kSkipFunctionTypesInTypeSection && module_->has_signature(i) &&
842 !in_explicit_recgroup) {
843 continue;
844 }
845 PrintTypeDefinition(i, indentation, kIndicesAsComments);
846 if (in_explicit_recgroup && i == recgroup.end_type_index - 1) {
847 in_explicit_recgroup = false;
848 indentation.decrease();
849 // The end of a recgroup is implicit in the wire bytes, so repeat the
850 // previous line's offset for it.
851 uint32_t offset = out_.current_line_bytecode_offset();
852 out_.NextLine(offset);
853 out_ << indentation << ")";
854 recgroup = offsets_->recgroup(recgroup_index++);
855 }
856 }
857 while (recgroup.valid()) {
858 // There could be empty recgroups at the end of the type section.
859 DCHECK_GE(recgroup.start_type_index, module_->types.size());
860 DCHECK_EQ(recgroup.start_type_index, recgroup.end_type_index);
861 out_.NextLine(recgroup.offset);
862 out_ << indentation << "(rec)";
863 recgroup = offsets_->recgroup(recgroup_index++);
864 }
865
866 // III. Imports
867 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < module_->import_table.size(); i++) {
868 const WasmImport& import = module_->import_table[i];
869 out_.NextLine(offsets_->import_offset(i));
870 out_ << indentation;
871 switch (import.kind) {
872 case kExternalTable: {
873 out_ << "(table ";
874 names_->PrintTableName(out_, import.index, kIndicesAsComments);
875 const WasmTable& table = module_->tables[import.index];
876 if (table.exported) PrintExportName(kExternalTable, import.index);
877 PrintImportName(import);
878 PrintTable(table);
879 break;
880 }
881 case kExternalFunction: {
882 out_ << "(func ";
883 names_->PrintFunctionName(out_, import.index, NamesProvider::kDevTools,
884 kIndicesAsComments);
885 const WasmFunction& func = module_->functions[import.index];
886 if (func.exported) PrintExportName(kExternalFunction, import.index);
887 PrintImportName(import);
888 PrintSignatureOneLine(out_, func.sig, import.index, names_, false);
889 break;
890 }
891 case kExternalGlobal: {
892 out_ << "(global ";
893 names_->PrintGlobalName(out_, import.index, kIndicesAsComments);
894 const WasmGlobal& global = module_->globals[import.index];
895 if (global.exported) PrintExportName(kExternalGlobal, import.index);
896 PrintImportName(import);
897 PrintGlobal(global);
898 break;
899 }
900 case kExternalMemory:
901 out_ << "(memory ";
902 names_->PrintMemoryName(out_, import.index, kIndicesAsComments);
903 if (module_->memories[import.index].exported) {
904 PrintExportName(kExternalMemory, 0);
905 }
906 PrintImportName(import);
907 PrintMemory(module_->memories[import.index]);
908 break;
909 case kExternalTag:
910 out_ << "(tag ";
911 names_->PrintTagName(out_, import.index, kIndicesAsComments);
912 PrintImportName(import);
913 if (exported_tags[import.index]) {
914 PrintExportName(kExternalTag, import.index);
915 }
916 PrintTagSignature(module_->tags[import.index].sig);
917 break;
918 }
919 out_ << ")";
920 }
921
922 // IV. Tables
923 for (uint32_t i = module_->num_imported_tables; i < module_->tables.size();
924 i++) {
925 const WasmTable& table = module_->tables[i];
926 DCHECK(!table.imported);
927 out_.NextLine(offsets_->table_offset(i));
928 out_ << indentation << "(table ";
929 names_->PrintTableName(out_, i, kIndicesAsComments);
930 if (table.exported) PrintExportName(kExternalTable, i);
931 PrintTable(table);
932 out_ << ")";
933 }
934
935 // V. Memories
936 uint32_t num_memories = static_cast<uint32_t>(module_->memories.size());
937 for (uint32_t memory_index = 0; memory_index < num_memories; ++memory_index) {
938 const WasmMemory& memory = module_->memories[memory_index];
939 if (memory.imported) continue;
940 out_.NextLine(offsets_->memory_offset());
941 out_ << indentation << "(memory ";
942 names_->PrintMemoryName(out_, memory_index, kIndicesAsComments);
943 if (memory.exported) PrintExportName(kExternalMemory, memory_index);
944 PrintMemory(memory);
945 out_ << ")";
946 }
947
948 // VI.Tags
949 for (uint32_t i = module_->num_imported_tags; i < module_->tags.size(); i++) {
950 const WasmTag& tag = module_->tags[i];
951 out_.NextLine(offsets_->tag_offset(i));
952 out_ << indentation << "(tag ";
953 names_->PrintTagName(out_, i, kIndicesAsComments);
954 if (exported_tags[i]) PrintExportName(kExternalTag, i);
955 PrintTagSignature(tag.sig);
956 out_ << ")";
957 }
958
959 // VII. String literals
960 size_t num_strings = module_->stringref_literals.size();
961 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_strings; i++) {
962 const WasmStringRefLiteral lit = module_->stringref_literals[i];
963 out_.NextLine(offsets_->string_offset(i));
964 out_ << indentation << "(string \"";
965 PrintString(lit.source);
966 out_ << '"';
967 if (kIndicesAsComments) out_ << " (;" << i << ";)";
968 out_ << ")";
969 }
970
971 // VIII. Globals
972 for (uint32_t i = module_->num_imported_globals; i < module_->globals.size();
973 i++) {
974 const WasmGlobal& global = module_->globals[i];
975 DCHECK(!global.imported);
976 out_.NextLine(offsets_->global_offset(i));
977 out_ << indentation << "(global ";
978 names_->PrintGlobalName(out_, i, kIndicesAsComments);
979 if (global.exported) PrintExportName(kExternalGlobal, i);
980 PrintGlobal(global);
981 PrintInitExpression(global.init, global.type);
982 out_ << ")";
983 }
984
985 // IX. Start
986 if (module_->start_function_index >= 0) {
987 out_.NextLine(offsets_->start_offset());
988 out_ << indentation << "(start ";
989 names_->PrintFunctionName(out_, module_->start_function_index,
990 NamesProvider::kDevTools);
991 out_ << ")";
992 }
993
994 // X. Elements
995 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < module_->elem_segments.size(); i++) {
996 const WasmElemSegment& elem = module_->elem_segments[i];
997 out_.NextLine(offsets_->element_offset(i));
998 out_ << indentation << "(elem ";
999 names_->PrintElementSegmentName(out_, i, kIndicesAsComments);
1000 if (elem.status == WasmElemSegment::kStatusDeclarative) {
1001 out_ << " declare";
1002 } else if (elem.status == WasmElemSegment::kStatusActive) {
1003 if (elem.table_index != 0) {
1004 out_ << " (table ";
1005 names_->PrintTableName(out_, elem.table_index);
1006 out_ << ")";
1007 }
1008 PrintInitExpression(elem.offset, kWasmI32);
1009 }
1010 out_ << " ";
1011 if (elem.shared) out_ << "shared ";
1012 names_->PrintValueType(out_, elem.type);
1013
1014 ModuleDecoderImpl decoder(WasmFeatures::All(), wire_bytes_.module_bytes(),
1015 ModuleOrigin::kWasmOrigin);
1016 decoder.consume_bytes(elem.elements_wire_bytes_offset);
1017 for (size_t i = 0; i < elem.element_count; i++) {
1018 ConstantExpression entry = decoder.consume_element_segment_entry(
1019 const_cast<WasmModule*>(module_), elem);
1020 PrintInitExpression(entry, elem.type);
1021 }
1022 out_ << ")";
1023 }
1024
1025 // For the FunctionBodyDisassembler, we flip the convention: {NextLine} is
1026 // now called *after* printing something, instead of before.
1027 if (out_.length() != 0) out_.NextLine(0);
1028
1029 // XI. Code / function bodies.
1030 if (function_body_offsets_ != nullptr) {
1031 size_t num_defined_functions =
1032 module_->functions.size() - module_->num_imported_functions;
1033 function_body_offsets_->reserve(num_defined_functions * 2);
1034 }
1035 for (uint32_t i = module_->num_imported_functions;
1036 i < module_->functions.size(); i++) {
1037 const WasmFunction* func = &module_->functions[i];
1038 out_.set_current_line_bytecode_offset(func->code.offset());
1039 out_ << indentation << "(func ";
1040 names_->PrintFunctionName(out_, i, NamesProvider::kDevTools,
1041 kIndicesAsComments);
1042 if (func->exported) PrintExportName(kExternalFunction, i);
1043 PrintSignatureOneLine(out_, func->sig, i, names_, true, kIndicesAsComments);
1044 out_.NextLine(func->code.offset());
1045 bool shared = module_->types[func->sig_index].is_shared;
1046 WasmFeatures detected;
1047 base::Vector<const uint8_t> code = wire_bytes_.GetFunctionBytes(func);
1048 FunctionBodyDisassembler d(&zone_, module_, i, shared, &detected, func->sig,
1049 code.begin(), code.end(), func->code.offset(),
1050 wire_bytes_, names_);
1051 uint32_t first_instruction_offset;
1052 d.DecodeAsWat(out_, indentation, FunctionBodyDisassembler::kSkipHeader,
1053 &first_instruction_offset);
1054 if (function_body_offsets_ != nullptr) {
1055 function_body_offsets_->push_back(first_instruction_offset);
1056 function_body_offsets_->push_back(d.pc_offset());
1057 }
1058 if (out_.ApproximateSizeMB() > max_mb) {
1059 out_ << "<truncated...>";
1060 return;
1061 }
1062 }
1063
1064 // XII. Data
1065 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < module_->data_segments.size(); i++) {
1066 const WasmDataSegment& data = module_->data_segments[i];
1067 out_.set_current_line_bytecode_offset(offsets_->data_offset(i));
1068 out_ << indentation << "(data";
1069 if (!kSkipDataSegmentNames) {
1070 out_ << " ";
1071 names_->PrintDataSegmentName(out_, i, kIndicesAsComments);
1072 }
1073 if (data.shared) out_ << " shared";
1074 if (data.active) {
1075 ValueType type = module_->memories[data.memory_index].is_memory64
1076 ? kWasmI64
1077 : kWasmI32;
1078 PrintInitExpression(data.dest_addr, type);
1079 }
1080 out_ << " \"";
1081 PrintString(data.source);
1082 out_ << "\")";
1083 out_.NextLine(0);
1084
1085 if (out_.ApproximateSizeMB() > max_mb) {
1086 out_ << "<truncated...>";
1087 return;
1088 }
1089 }
1090
1091 indentation.decrease();
1092 out_.set_current_line_bytecode_offset(
1093 static_cast<uint32_t>(wire_bytes_.length()));
1094 out_ << indentation << ")"; // End of the module.
1095 out_.NextLine(0);
1096}

1141void ModuleDisassembler::PrintInitExpression(const ConstantExpression& init,
1142 ValueType expected_type) {
1143 switch (init.kind()) {
1144 case ConstantExpression::kEmpty:
1145 break;
1146 case ConstantExpression::kI32Const:
1147 out_ << " (i32.const " << init.i32_value() << ")";
1148 break;
1149 case ConstantExpression::kRefNull:
1150 out_ << " (ref.null ";
1151 names_->PrintHeapType(out_, HeapType(init.repr()));
1152 out_ << ")";
1153 break;
1154 case ConstantExpression::kRefFunc:
1155 out_ << " (ref.func ";
1156 names_->PrintFunctionName(out_, init.index(), NamesProvider::kDevTools);
1157 out_ << ")";
1158 break;
1159 case ConstantExpression::kWireBytesRef:
1160 WireBytesRef ref = init.wire_bytes_ref();
1161 const uint8_t* start = start_ + ref.offset();
1162 const uint8_t* end = start_ + ref.end_offset();
1163
1164 auto sig = FixedSizeSignature<ValueType>::Returns(expected_type);
1165 WasmFeatures detected;
1166 FunctionBodyDisassembler d(&zone_, module_, 0, false, &detected, &sig,
1167 start, end, ref.offset(), wire_bytes_, names_);
1168 d.DecodeGlobalInitializer(out_);
1169 break;
1170 }
1171}

1175 out_ << " (param ";
1176 names_->PrintValueType(out_, sig->GetParam(i));
1177 out_ << ")";
1178 }

1185// This mimics legacy wasmparser behavior. It might be a questionable choice,
1186// but we'll follow suit for now.
1187void ModuleDisassembler::PrintStringAsJSON(WireBytesRef ref) {
1188 for (const uint8_t* ptr = start_ + ref.offset();
1189 ptr < start_ + ref.end_offset(); ptr++) {
1190 uint8_t b = *ptr;
1191 if (b <= 34) {
1192 switch (b) {
1193 // clang-format off
1194 case '\b': out_ << "\\b"; break;
1195 case '\t': out_ << "\\t"; break;
1196 case '\n': out_ << "\\n"; break;
1197 case '\f': out_ << "\\f"; break;
1198 case '\r': out_ << "\\r"; break;
1199 case ' ': out_ << ' '; break;
1200 case '!': out_ << '!'; break;
1201 case '"': out_ << "\\\""; break;
1202 // clang-format on
1203 default:
1204 out_ << "\\u00" << kHexChars[b >> 4] << kHexChars[b & 0xF];
1205 break;
1206 }
1207 } else if (b != 127 && b != '\\') {
1208 out_ << static_cast<char>(b);
1209 } else if (b == '\\') {
1210 out_ << "\\\\";
1211 } else {
1212 out_ << "\\x7F";
1213 }
1214 }
1215}
1216
1217void ModuleDisassembler::LineBreakOrSpace(bool break_lines,
1218 Indentation indentation,
1219 uint32_t byte_offset) {
1220 if (break_lines) {
1221 out_.NextLine(byte_offset);
1222 out_ << indentation.Extra(2);
1223 } else {
1224 out_ << " ";
1225 }
1226}
